The paper discusses Collaborative Question Answering (CQA) frameworks for knowledge graphs, which involves integrating existing question answering (QA) components for implementing sequences of QA tasks. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-categories in computer science, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Databases (cs.DB), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Given that the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for optimizing CQA frameworks, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. However, cs.CL, cs.DB, and cs.IR are also relevant as they deal with natural language processing, data management, and information retrieval, respectively.
